For sale is an excellent condition Smith and Wesson 629-4 classic (pre-lock) 44 mag/spl with 6.5 inch full lug ported barrel.   This Mod. 629 has the -4 designation which is the last dash model that is pre-lock and pre-MIM (forged hammer & trigger) revolver with the complete factory Endurance Package. The endurance package was created in response to silhouette shooters who were using heavy bullets loaded as fast as possible. S&W simply beefed up these revolvers to last a lot longer and to be able to take more of a beating. It entails as follows: hardened hand & bolt, hardened retention system on the yoke/cylinder crane, hardened yoke and frame, radius-ed internal studs, and elongated bolt cuts on the cylinder.This revolver is a tack driver and would make a great deer gun or plinker.

There is an eagle over swastika proof on the frame just under the slide release and very, very faint evidence of what should be the same proof over the slide release on the slide itself. Barrel also looks to have faint proof ahead of the serial. Only other visible stamp is MP on the front of the trigger guard. Pistol looks to have original grips in great shape.
